                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d516">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/7453</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-10-26T18:00:00-03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 27, 6.45 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At 20 minutes to 6 this afternoon the Senate unanimously voted the following
                    resolution which the Chamber had approved at 3 o’clock: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>A state of war between Brazil and the German Empire, provoked by the
                            latter, is hereby recognized and proclaimed and the President of the
                            Republic, in accordance with the request contained in his message to the
                            National Congress, is hereby authorized to take such steps for the
                            National defense and public safety as he shall consider adequate, to
                            open the necessary credits and to authorize the credit operations
                            required. All previous measures to; the contrary are hereby revoked.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MEV1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
